      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of August 14 Business Day article on controversy over reporting of ABC's consumer and environmental correspondent, John Stossel</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Business Day yesterday about controversy over the reporting of ABC's consumer and environmental correspondent, John Stossel, misspelled the surname of a senior fellow at the Manhattan Institute who has defended Mr. Stossel. The defender is Walter Olson, not Olsen.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article in Business Day yesterday about controversy over the reporting of ABC's consumer and environmental correspondent, John Stossel, misspelled the surname of a senior fellow at the Manhattan Institute who has defended Mr. Stossel. The defender is Walter Olson, not Olsen.</p>
      </block>
